g.text: The dataset is adopted from a Multi-omics study of Covid-19 patients [4].

•Use the Investigation-Study-Assay (ISA) framework [5] to capture experimental metadata. •A Jupyter Notebook[6] was created as a possible template for the creation of ISA-Tab files for multi-omics (meta)data.
Use ISA-API [7] to convert ISA-JSON to ISA-JSON-LD
Use Phenopacket[8] to capture information from TWOC Phenotype data, specifically converts each sample in the dataset to a PhenopacketsIndividual.
•Semantic searches on samples, phenotypes, omics measurements, and features are supported. •Federated SPARQL query is also supported [10].
AFDP instance [9] is set up which consist of a knowledge graph and aFDP client.
